HEADWORD: Polytheism
<hw>Pol"y*the*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Poly-</ets> + Gr. <?/ cf. F.
<ets>polyth⟦eacute⟧isme</ets>.]</ety> <def>The doctrine of, or belief
in, a plurality of gods.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>In the Old Testament, the gradual development of
<qex>polytheism</qex> from the primitive monotheism may be learned.</q>
<rj><qau>Shaff-Herzog.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Polytheist</ent>⟦br⟧
